# node-linker=hoisted — REQUIRED for the bundled CcResDoc.app to work.
#
# The Tauri host bundles app/ (incl. node_modules) into the .app and copies it
# to a writable workspace at runtime. Tauri's resource copy DEREFERENCES
# symlinks, which destroys pnpm's default isolated `.pnpm` store structure —
# transitive deps (e.g. `hono`, pulled in by @takazudo/zfb-runtime's router)
# then become unresolvable, the zfb renderer is disabled, and every content
# page 404s. A hoisted (flat, npm-style) node_modules has every package as a
# real top-level dir, so the dereferencing copy yields a complete, resolvable
# tree. This is why app/ is a STANDALONE pnpm project (not a workspace member):
# node-linker is workspace-global, and a workspace would hoist into the repo
# root node_modules instead of app/node_modules (which is what gets bundled).
node-linker=hoisted
